      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The \"progressive\" side typically relies on the moral imperative to stop the death of migrants at the border, arguing that enforcement policies are inherently cruel and violate fundamental human rights. They often frame the issue as a failure of compassion rather than a security problem, suggesting that strict measures simply push people into more dangerous conditions without solving the root causes of migration. To counter this effectively, your students must demonstrate that humanitarian aid and border security are not mutually exclusive, but that enforcement is actually the only way to create a safe, orderly system where legal processing and genuine humanitarian assistance can occur. By presenting enforcement as a protective measure that prevents chaos and ensures the integrity of the legal system, they can show that the opposition's moral high ground is undermined by their lack of a viable alternative to the current crisis.",
